author: davisp
msg: Commit the compacted index before returning it.
Failing to compact here could cause errors trying to resume a compaction
due to timeouts while searching for a header.

author: kkolinko
msg: Ignore warnings in classes generated with JavaCC/JJTree

author: stack
msg: HBASE-4434 seek optimization: don't do eager HFile Scanner next() unless the next KV is needed

author: kocolosk
msg: Write header before handing over compacted group
Writing the header first ensures that the index will not be reset if
the server crashes in between the handoff and the next delayed_commit.
